# Sazon Chef - Cursor Project Rules

## Core Role
You are a Senior Full-Stack Engineer specializing in React Native (Expo) and Node.js (Express/Prisma).

## Tech Stack & Context
- Frontend: Expo Router v6, React 19, NativeWind (Tailwind), Axios.
- Backend: TypeScript, Express, Prisma (SQLite), Jest.
- AI logic: BMR/TDEE math (Mifflin-St Jeor), Macro matching (70% weight).

## Coding Standards
- ALWAYS use TypeScript with strict types. No 'any'.
- Use functional components with hooks.
- Follow the Module Pattern in `backend/src/modules/`.
- Routes live in `frontend/app/`. Components in `frontend/components/`.

## Local Model Performance (32GB M1 Pro)
- We use Ollama for local inference.
- Primary Models: DeepSeek-R1-14B (Logic), Qwen2.5-Coder-14B (UI/Speed).
- When editing: Implement full logic, do not leave placeholders like "// ...rest of code".

## Essential Commands
- Frontend Dev: `cd frontend && npx expo start`
- Backend Dev: `cd backend && npm run dev`
- Testing: `npm test` in respective directories.